scene.message:
Maki: I hope Chisato and Naito{nl}
work out well.{waitkey}{clearbox}It's not sour grapes or{nl}
anything{wait_fr:32}... because {wait_fr:32}I...{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Is he locking us in to{nl}
toy with us? Or stalling for{nl}
time?{waitkey}I can't read his intent.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: This time we'll get a{nl}
proper talk out of her,{nl}
I trust.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: The more one tries to{nl}
bottle up their feelings, the{nl}
bigger they explode in the{nl}
end.{waitkey}{clearbox}Though with you, there's no{nl}
such worry!{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: That Aki — using even{nl}
Kozai now, what's he{nl}
plotting?{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: When you think it's a{nl}
road you've walked before,{nl}
doesn't it feel shorter?{wait_fr:48}{nl}
...No, I suppose not...{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: Oh Queen~! I've been{nl}
looking forward to meeting{nl}
you~♥{waitkey}Is that a good enough{nl}
greeting?{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: Kozai made one heck of{nl}
a room...{waitkey}{clearbox}Imagining myself turned into{nl}
one of those things in{nl}
there... yeesh, that's rough!{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: Well, the point is{nl}
don't sweat the small stuff~!{waitkey}{clearbox}Huh? I should worry more?{nl}
Okay, okay! Leave it to me~!{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: That Queen, is she{nl}
trying to set up an idol{nl}
training school or something?{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: No matter how much you{nl}
think it over, what you don't{nl}
know, you don't know!{waitkey}{clearbox}Anyway, we track down where{nl}
this so-called Queen is.{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: If you get hurt over{nl}
every little thing like this,{nl}
you'll never make it in the{nl}
world.{waitkey}{clearbox}There are plenty of people{nl}
who've been through far{nl}
worse.{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: What is it? You think{nl}
I'm going to say I was{nl}
"moved"?{waitkey}{ret}

Young Man: This is a painting{nl}
the Queen made. It's kinda{nl}
nice, isn't it...{waitkey}{clearbox}The Queen paints well and{nl}
she's a beauty{wait_fr:32}... but I'm{nl}
good-looking too, right?{waitkey}{ret}

Young Man: You know what I{nl}
think? What's even good about{nl}
a painting like this?{waitkey}{clearbox}Putting on airs as a "Queen"{nl}
and all — I'm way more{nl}
charming than her!{waitkey}{ret}

There's a painting said to be{nl}
the Queen's work.{wait_fr:21}...The style{nl}
looks like something you've{nl}
seen somewhere before.{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: ...{wait_fr:32}This painting...!{wait_fr:48}{nl}
This is a painting Chisato{nl}
made...!{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Chisato — {wait_fr:21}Chisato{nl}
Kozai? I heard she went{nl}
missing!{waitkey}{clearbox}Kozai's painting is here, and{nl}
it's supposed to be the{nl}
Queen's painting...?{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: Why?{wait_fr:48} Does that mean{nl}
Chisato is being held by the{nl}
Harem Queen...?{wait_fr:32}{waitkey}{ret}
